      • getName

        public java.lang.String getName()

      • getObjective

      • setValue

        public void setValue​(java.lang.String valueIn)
        Sets the value that is displayed for the score. Generally, you do not want to call this as the score is resolved automatically. (If you want to manually set text, use a TextComponentString)

      • getUnformattedComponentText

        public java.lang.String getUnformattedComponentText()
        Gets the raw content of this component (but not its sibling components), without any formatting codes. For example, this is the raw text in a TextComponentString, but it's the translated text for a TextComponentTranslation and it's the score value for a TextComponentScore.

      • resolve

        public void resolve​(ICommandSender sender)
        Resolves the value of the score on this component.

      • createCopy

        public TextComponentScore createCopy()
        Creates a copy of this component. Almost a deep copy, except the style is shallow-copied.
